Abuja – The Senate yesterday appointed Senator Adedayo Adeyeye (APC Ekiti South) as the chairman, Senate Ad Hoc Committee on Media and Public Affairs.
The President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, who presided over the plenary on Wednesday, made the announcement.
The President of the Senate also named Senators Uba Sani (APC Kaduna Central), Abba Moro (PDP Benue South), Ifeanyi Uba (YPP Anambra South) and Betty Apiafi (PDP Rivers West) as members.
Recall that Adeyeye was a former Minister of State for Works and also the past spokesman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) before he defected to the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC).
He was also the pioneer spokesman of Afenifere, a Yoruba socio-cultural group during the dark days of former Head of State, late General Sani Abacha between 1993 and 1998.
The lawmaker replaced the immediate past Senate Minority Leader, Senator Biodun Olujimi, having defeated her in the last general elections in Ekiti State.